PR8 Gaussian lifecycle observation patch
=======================================

This patch is applied after PR7 training events:

  python scripts/third_party/apply_gaussian_splatting_observation_patch.py \
    --third-party-root ./third_party \
    --patch pr8_gaussian_lifecycle

The generated patch adds marker-delimited, observation-only lifecycle hooks to:

  third_party/gaussian-splatting/train.py
  third_party/gaussian-splatting/scene/gaussian_model.py

Markers:

  # VIEWTRUST PR8 GAUSSIAN LIFECYCLE START
  # VIEWTRUST PR8 GAUSSIAN LIFECYCLE END

PR8 depends on the PR7 patch because it reuses PR7 child-environment setup and
Gaussian count helpers in train.py. It is intentionally separate so an existing
server checkout with old PR7 already applied can be upgraded without restoring
the whole trainer first.

Safety policy:

  - no loss changes
  - no optimizer behavior changes
  - no camera sampling changes
  - no rendering changes
  - no densification threshold or decision changes
  - no pruning or opacity reset decision changes
  - lifecycle IDs are non-trainable Python metadata
  - no third_party source is committed to ViewTrust-GS

The observer activates only when:

  VIEWTRUST_ENABLE_GAUSSIAN_LIFECYCLE=1

Otherwise the official trainer should behave as before.
